Dear Sir or Madam: 
 
You appear to be responsible for the IP address through which the web
site "www.strumpette.com" is available.  That site currently has posted
a fake news article that it is attributing to The Associated Press (see
http://www.strumpette.com/archives/270-BREAKING-NEWS-Strumpette-Injured-

in-Rollover-Crash.html and the second article on the main page).   
 
Unfortunately, does not contain any contact information, so I must
request that you contact the owner of the site to have AP's trademark
removed from these stories.  AP takes no position on the text of the
story and does not wish to have the site or the story taken down.  AP
only insists that its name be removed from a story that was not written
by The Associated Press. 
 
Thanks.  If you have any questions, please contact me at the number
below. 
 
Sincerely, 
 
George Galt
Associate General Counsel
The Associated Press  
1825 K St. N.W., Suite 800   
Washington DC  20006
